HEADWORD: Submediant
<hw>Sub*me"di*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>The sixth tone of the scale; the under mediant, or third below the
keynote; the superdominant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

